comment_data.body:
No strong opinion. 

```
/// Checks if time `tm1` is equal to `tm2`.
///
/// @return true if `tm1` == `tm2`
static bool profile_equal(proftime_T tm1, proftime_T tm2) FUNC_ATTR_CONST
{
  return tm1 == tm2;
}
```

if that function was more complicated, i may reconsider.
Basic equality check is enough to shim `profile_equal()` outside C codebase.

